{"user_message": {"title": "Code Review — REQUEST_CHANGES — ADR 0002 banker's rounding (commit b29eeaa)", "content": "## Code Review — Verdict: **REQUEST_CHANGES**\n\nReviewed commit `b29eeaa` (ADR 0002, currency-aware banker's rounding) on `ai-bookkeeper`. The rounding logic is high quality and the suite is green (25/25), but the commit is **not self-contained** — it breaks a clean checkout. That gates the verdict.\n\n### Critical\n- **`src/features/ledger/index.ts:4` & `:20` — barrel re-exports from untracked modules — _build breaks on fresh checkout / CI._** Commit `b29eeaa` added `export { ... } from \"./lib/amount\"` and `export { ... } from \"./lib/ingest\"`, but `git log` shows **neither file has ever been committed** (both are `??` untracked in the working tree). The parent barrel had only 3 lines, so this commit *introduced* the dangling references. Tests pass locally only because the files happen to exist in the working tree; a clean clone of `b29eeaa` will fail `tsc --noEmit` and module resolution.\n  - **Fix:** Land `src/features/ledger/lib/amount.ts`, `amount.test.ts`, and `ingest.ts` as a prerequisite commit (ADR 0001 work) **before** `b29eeaa` reaches `main` — or stack `b29eeaa` on top of a PR that commits them. Alternatively, narrow the barrel to only export `./lib/round` until the siblings land. Do not leave `main` with a barrel pointing at files not in the tree.\n\n### Low / Notes (non-gating)\n- `src/features/ledger/lib/round.ts:89` — the `HALF_EPSILON = 1e-9` tie window admits a theoretical misclassification band of ~1e-11 in value units (e.g. `0.025 + 1e-11` would round to even rather than up). This is far below monetary input precision and is the correct trade-off for catching FP near-ties like `2.675`. Documented in the file. **No change required** — noted for the record.\n- `src/features/ledger/lib/amount.ts` `roundToCents` (half-up) still diverges from `roundMoney` (half-even). This is the documented, deferred Task 4 (blocked on first aggregation consumer) — correctly out of scope, not a regression.\n- **Config note (operational, not code):** the codebase credential is labeled `ai-paralegal` but resolves to `ai-bookkeeper`. Worth correcting the label to avoid confusion in future handoffs.\n\n### What's correct (verified)\n- `roundMoney` half-even logic checked across positive, negative, zero (`-0`→`0`), zero-decimal (JPY), three-decimal (BHD), large-magnitude, and unknown/case-insensitive codes — all correct.\n- Fail-loud on non-finite `value` and blank `currency` (`RangeError`), consistent with the ledger's input boundary in `amount.ts`.\n- Pure, side-effect-free, well-documented; matches repo conventions.\n- `npm test` → **25/25 green**.\n\n### Verdict: **REQUEST_CHANGES**\nReason: a Critical build-integrity defect (barrel references untracked `amount.ts`/`ingest.ts`). The rounding module is otherwise approvable — resolve the prerequisite-commit issue and this clears.", "content_type": "warning", "priority": "high"}}

